	   <tr><td colspan=2>Just to bring this debate to a close...<br><br>I'd say everybody has to come to their own conclusions.&nbsp;&nbsp;The game for rogues changes a lot from lvl 1 to lvl 60.  What you need at 15th lvl probably isn't the same thing you need a 60th lvl (as far as your main focus... AC, AGI, Resists, STR, etc.)<br><br>Everybody made some valid points... even Restyn!  ;-)<br><br>This board will never provide all of the answers, but as long as we keep debating these issues, we'll at least come a little closer to some of the answers.<br><br>But, regardless of how you play your rogue... from a light, sneaky and elusive parrying rogue, to a muscle-bound heavy hitter, be proud of your class.  I am convinced there is no other class that offers as much excitement, and does as much overall damage as the Rogue.<br>&nbsp;<br>Fluxus<br>58 Rogue<br>Tarew Marr<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=138160" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=138160</a></td></tr>
